The job in short

The Financial Services world is being disrupted by new digital-first technologies and business models (Fintechs), and we are at the heart of this massive industry transformation. We partner with more than 120 banks around the world, providing state-of-the-art digital technology and transformation expertise.

As the Digital Transformation Director, you'll be responsible for strategic digital advisory to our clients and subsequently taking the ownership for the delivery and execution of digital transformation initiatives.

You'll leverage your deep digital transformation expertise and consulting / execution management skills to help banking CEOs and their teams solve their most pressing challenges, focusing on how digital and technology will change the shape of their business.

Meet the job

You will be building Strategic Executive Relations with our clients: we work with the largest banks in the world, who rely on Backbase as their trusted advisor and committed partner to help them successfully execute their digital transformation.

You will help customers define their digital transformation roadmap: this requires the ability to work with clients in a consultative way; helping customers translate their business objectives into digital strategies.

You will deliver efficient and high-quality professional services: You help customers successfully execute a portfolio of digital projects and you take ownership of end-2-end project implementations (large scale projects).

You will promote Customer Success Stories and best practices across the company: by celebrating and promoting the success of our customers and creating Customer Success testimonials. Drive the definition of the ideal customer types and the associated best practices for implementation and growth.

How about you?

You have 6+ years experience in Digital Strategy and Delivery;
You will have previously worked with or for major Digital Transformation Consultancy businesses, or in a large enterprise leading digital initiatives;
You have extensive experience in working with multi-skilled digital teams (Architects, Project Managers, UX Designers, Software Engineers and QA Engineers);
You have a strong understanding of business transformation, digital, Agile software development and change delivery;
You have a strong ability to work with both business and technology stakeholders;
You have an entrepreneurial drive, with the ability to deconstruct and solve problems, to investigate drivers and figure out why things happen;
You have proven ability to build strong relationships across stakeholder groups, with the ability to effectively influence and communicate across various business units and at senior levels within the organisation;
You have a deep understanding of the digital industry, and the issues and opportunities its players face in areas such as technology, data and business change;
You are an enthusiastic and creative leader with the ability to inspire others;
You have excellent communication and presentation skills.

